.SH NAME
ftpcp - copy files from a FTP server to the local machine
.LINE
.section SYNOPSIS
ftpcp ftp://host[:port]/directory local-dir
.paragraph
or
.paragraph
ftpcp host[:post] /directory local-dir
.section DESCRIPTION
\fBftpcp\fR is a frontend to the \fBftpcopy\fR program. Calling
.paragraph
  ftpcp arguments ...
.paragraph
has exactly the same results as calling
.paragraph
  ftpcopy -n arguments ...
.paragraph
or, in other words: \fBftpcp\fR calls \fBftpcopy\fR \fI-n\fR, so that files
already in the local directory are not deleted.
